    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nI'm having a hard time mapping leader to special characters using Lua, but it works in VimScript\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n**This works**\r\n```\r\nvim.cmd([[\r\n  let mapleader = \"\\<cr>\"\r\n  let maplocalleader = \"\\<space>\"\r\n]])\r\n```\r\n\r\n**This does not work**\r\n```\r\nvim.g.mapleader = \"\\<cr>\"\r\nvim.g.maplocalleader = \"\\<space>\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n- I would expect them to work the same.\r\n- It would be nice if the documentation for mapleader covered special characters\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.9.4\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 14.1\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nKitty/0.31.0\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nhomebrew",
    "closed_at": null,
