            "body": "> What you want to do can be accomplished by using the lua \" \" (space) and \"\\r\" (carriage return) strings\r\n\r\nThe only problem with this is that `\" \"` could look like any type of whitespace, like a tab. Granted, I know the solution for that would be to probably use `\"\\t\"` instead, but having some other way to express `\" \"` like `<space>` would be _really_ nice here.\r\n\r\n**ETA:** I did find that I could use `\"\\u{20}\"` or `\"\\32\"` (hex `20`) to be more explicit. Not sure if this helps with the readability, though ðŸ˜… ",
